"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760217","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The Treaty will provide a framework for defence cooperation that includes a range of areas where we may wish to work together, such as training, exercises, sharing information and defence industry.</p><p>The text for the Treaty is still under negotiation and it would therefore be inappropriate to comment in further detail.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-10T14:54:19.69Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760217/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760217/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760217/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Poland: Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what specific areas of co-operation will be covered by the UK's defence co-operation treaty with Poland announced in the joint communiqué issued in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","10469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760218","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The UK and Poland have a strong bilateral relationship; we have approximately 150 UK troops deployed to Poland on a persistent basis as part of enhanced Forward Presence. We are both important members of NATO. The UK/Poland bilateral Defence Cooperation Treaty will provide a framework for collaboration that is complementary to our work in NATO but in no way supersedes it. We have other bilateral treaties with NATO Allies, such as France, which work in a similar manner.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-10T14:42:24.65Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760218/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760218/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760218/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Poland: Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the added value a bilateral defence co-operation treaty with Poland will bring to existing NATO guarantees between the UK and Poland.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","10470"
