he will provide the data set out in tables 6, 7 and 10 of the document entitled MoD Regional Expenditure with UK Industry and Commerce and Supported Employment 2015-16 as it relates to Scotland.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","10488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760220","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-09","<p>As outlined in the Defence Equipment Plan Report 2016 we intend to spend around £19 billion on building ships and submarines and £44 billion on supporting ships and submarines over the next 10 years, totalling £63 billion. As outlined in the report, for ships this includes the completion of the new Queen Elizabeth Aircraft Carriers, the construction of the Type 26 frigate, four new Tide Class tankers, new Offshore Patrol Vessels and the implementation of a Common Support Model. For submarines it includes support to those in service, delivery of the Astute and Dreadnought submarine programmes and the Nuclear Warhead Capability Sustainment Programme, plus procurement of new nuclear propulsion plants.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-09T15:35:17.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760220/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760220/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760220/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 9, paragraph 13 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, how the figure of £63 billion of Government spending on procurement and support for surface ships and submarines was calculated.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760221","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The term points of presence refers to the locations in which we will wish the Royal Navy to provide support, be visible, engage and project influence, in order to deliver the National Security Strategy objectives and contribute to a Global Britain.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-10T14:40:52.59Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760221/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760221/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760221/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 9, paragraph 15 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, if he will define the term points of presence.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760222","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The figures referenced in the National Shipbuilding Strategy cannot be disaggregated by region. They are estimates for 2014, based on data from official sources. We also have statistics for 2012, which were published in the Maritime Growth Study.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","105046","2017-10-10T14:28:44.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760222/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760222/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760222/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 10, paragraph 16 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, if he will publish comparable statistics on the performance of the UK maritime and marine sectors for each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760223","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The UK continues its active commitment to NATO. Currently, one Type 45 destroyer and an offshore hydrographic survey vessel are performing the role of flagship for two Standing NATO Maritime Groups, with a mine counter measures vessel also contributing. In addition to the Standing NATO Maritime Groups, naval Service personnel from all arms of the Service regularly participate in NATO exercises.</p><p>For security reasons, we do not disclose the detail of the future scheduling of Royal Navy units, as this would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-10T14:46:55.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760223/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760223/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760223/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Type 23 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which of the currently operational Type 23 frigates are not planned to contribute to NATO's Standing Maritime Groups.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760224","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The sale of the Goliath crane is being managed by the Aircraft Carrier Alliance. There has been considerable interest in buying the crane and companies around the world have registered an interest, but to date there have been no representations from officials of other governments.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-10T14:31:51.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760224/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760224/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760224/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Rosyth Dockyard: Materials Handling Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what representations his Department received from officials of other governments on the sale of the Rosyth Goliath crane.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760225","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>Pre-procurement activity with industry has begun and will continue into early 2018 when we plan to formally start the competitive process. We plan to award a single design and build contract in 2019, allowing us to trial and accept the first ship into service in 2023.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-10T14:37:44.57Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760225/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760225/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760225/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Type 31 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the National Shipbuilding Strategy, what the timeframe is for the competition to build the Type 31e frigate.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760226","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The UK delegation will include military and Ministry of Defence (MOD) civilian personnel from the Counter-Proliferation and Arms Control Centre, Development Concepts and Doctrine Centre and Defence Science and Technology Laboratory. A priority for the MOD is to support the Foreign and Commonwealth Office in fulfilling our commitments as a proactive State Party to the CCW. MOD participation will allow us to share our thinking on autonomy, notably as set out in the recently published Unmanned Aerial Systems (UAS) doctrine note. This forms part of our efforts to build improved understanding at the international level in the debate on Armed Forces' use of remote and automated systems.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-10T14:53:46.623Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760226/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760226/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760226/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, who from his Department will represent the UK at the November meetings of the UN Convention on Certain Conventional Weapons in Geneva and Group of Governmental Experts on Lethal Autonomous Weapons; and what the priorities of those attending those meetings will be.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","105018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760227","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-09","<p>During the development of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, the Ministry of Defence engaged with the Trade Unions and will continue to do so.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-09T15:32:54.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760227/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760227/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760227/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 17, figure 2 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, what recent representation he has received from trade union officials regarding challenges related to procurement at pace.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760228","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>One of our key aims in procuring the Type 31e frigate is to minimise the cost of owning the ships. A key factor in achieving this aim will be keeping maintenance to a minimum and simplifying maintenance tasks wherever possible.</p><p>We expect that designing ease of maintenance into the ships from the outset will be highly attractive to potential export customers.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-10T14:36:51.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760228/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760228/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760228/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Type 31 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 24, paragraph 67 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, what plans are in place to develop exportable through life support solutions for Type 31e frigates built for foreign navies.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105052"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760229","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The figures referenced in the National Shipbuilding Strategy cannot be disaggregated by region. They are estimates for 2014, based on data from official sources. We also have statistics for 2012, which were published in the Maritime Growth Study.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","105044","2017-10-10T14:28:44.753Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760229/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760229/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 10, paragraph 16 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, what estimate he has made of the value of the UK maritime and marine sector by region.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760230","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-09","<p>The Government stands ready to consider the provision of export credit guarantees in support of the export of Type 31e on a case by case basis.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-09T15:31:36.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760230/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760230/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760230/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Type 31 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 27, chapter 4 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, whether he expects export credit guarantees to apply to Type 31e frigates exported to foreign navies.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760231","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-09","<p>The steel required for the construction of the Type 26 Frigates is sourced by our prime contractor, BAE Systems. UK suppliers are able to meet the specification for 50 per cent by value of the steel for the first batch of Type 26 Frigates and the steel is being sourced from mills in Scotland and Scunthorpe. The remaining steel required for the Type 26 Frigates cannot currently be sourced in the UK.</p><p>Approximately 3,800 tonnes of steel are required for the construction of each ship, including structural steel plate at a range of thicknesses (from less than six millimetres (mm) to over 20mm) and sectional steel including bulb, channel, equal and unequal angle, flat bar and IPE steel beams.</p><p>In respect of monitoring the sourcing of steel for warship programmes, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to Question 3946 on 18 July 2017 to the hon. Member for Aberavon (Stephen Kinnock).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","105055","2017-10-09T15:34:23.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760231/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760231/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 22, paragraph 55 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, what the rationale is for outlining a figure of 50 per cent total value for British made steel needed for Type 26 frigates; and if he will list the steels used to be used in that programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760232","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-09","<p>The steel required for the construction of the Type 26 Frigates is sourced by our prime contractor, BAE Systems. UK suppliers are able to meet the specification for 50 per cent by value of the steel for the first batch of Type 26 Frigates and the steel is being sourced from mills in Scotland and Scunthorpe. The remaining steel required for the Type 26 Frigates cannot currently be sourced in the UK.</p><p>Approximately 3,800 tonnes of steel are required for the construction of each ship, including structural steel plate at a range of thicknesses (from less than six millimetres (mm) to over 20mm) and sectional steel including bulb, channel, equal and unequal angle, flat bar and IPE steel beams.</p><p>In respect of monitoring the sourcing of steel for warship programmes, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to Question 3946 on 18 July 2017 to the hon. Member for Aberavon (Stephen Kinnock).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","105054","2017-10-09T15:34:23.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760232/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760232/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760232/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 22, paragraph 55 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, how his Department monitors the sourcing of steel for its warship programmes.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760233","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The detailed commercial arrangements have yet to be agreed but it is the intent to maximise the transfer of risk to the contractor during this programme, and minimise the dependencies that the Ministry of Defence will manage.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-10T14:38:41.963Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760233/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760233/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760233/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Type 31 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 18, paragraph 44 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, whether he expects that prime contractors will bear the cost of any programme cost overruns in the Type 31e programme following the main gate investment decision.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760234","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The National Shipbuilding Strategy makes clear that we judge that the capabilities the Royal Navy requires can be accommodated within this price, and our market research indicates that beyond this price the vessels would not be attractive to the sector of the export market we are targeting. We have conducted and shared market analysis with industry that reflects the Government's perspective of the international defence market place, and an assessment of the probability of success in securing customers.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-10T14:40:04.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760234/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760234/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760234/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Type 31 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 23, paragraph 61 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, what assessments contributed to the setting of a maximum £250 million per ship price for the Type 31e frigate.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760235","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-10","<p>The National Shipbuilding Strategy states, on page 21 paragraph 52, that the detailed Master Plan for internal use will not be publicly released. However, we have developed a public version (see Figure 3 of the Shipbuilding Strategy) which shows our broad thinking for the future fleet.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-10T14:36:01.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760235/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760235/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760235/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-13","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 13, paragraph 36 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy, whether the Master Plan for naval shipbuilding will be released into the pubic domain.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","105058"
