"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760237","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-09","<p>Natural England is currently collating the satellite tracking data on hen harriers from both before and since 2002. Natural England plans to publish the information shortly. There is also an independent analysis of all the satellite tracking data being undertaken, which is due for publication in spring 2018.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-10-09T10:52:23.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760237/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760237/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760237/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-13","Birds of Prey: Tagging","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will publish all the satellite tracking data of electronically tagged hen harriers collected by Natural England and its predecessor since 2002.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","10497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760238","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-09","<p>​On 21 September, I met the Cambodian Foreign Minister, Prak Sokhonn, at the UN General Assembly. I raised our concerns regarding the political situation in the country, including Kem Sokha's arrest. The UK urges the Government of Cambodia to take immediate steps to ensure free, fair and credible elections next year. We call for Kem Sokha to be released so that fully participatory legitimate elections can take place.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-10-09T15:41:00.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760238/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760238/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760238/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Kem Sokha","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Cambodian Government on the imprisonment of Kem Sokkha in Cambodia; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jo Swinson","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","105006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760240","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-09","<p>The FCO supports a number of programmes in these important areas. We are working with a range of Cambodian and international organisations to help strengthen the impact of their human rights work in Cambodia and are improving the capacity of regional networks in Cambodia to enhance their cooperation with the relevant authorities on governance and accountability.</p><p>Gender equality runs through all programmes supported by the FCO. In Cambodia we have focussed in particular on the Preventing Sexual Violence Initiative (PSVI), freedom of expression and women's involvement in politics. In line with our foreign policy priority to be a global leader in the fight against modern slavery, we are also supporting the development of a toolkit on how to properly collect and handle data for modern slavery cases which will be used by front line practitioners in government and civil society in Cambodia.</p><p>Additionally, the UK has for some years been one of the most active countries in supporting the Extraordinary Chambers in the Courts of Cambodia (ECCC) which is prosecuting the senior and most responsible Khmer Rouge leaders. This is being done through the UK's voluntary monetary contributions to the court and also through supporting awareness raising programmes across Cambodia to demonstrate the importance of the rule of law.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-10-09T15:46:18.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760240/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760240/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760240/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Cambodia: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what programmes his Department supports to promote human rights and the rule of law in Cambodia.","false","Biography information for Jo Swinson","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","105007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760241","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>Our Ambassador to Saudi Arabia raised the operation in Awamiyah with the Government of Saudi Arabia on 26 July, including measures to guard against civilian casualties. The Saudi authorities underlined the seriousness it placed on fulfilling its responsibilities to all its citizens, including the Shia. We continue to monitor the situation in Awamiyah closely and we will continue to raise legitimate concerns at every appropriate opportunity. The British Government strongly supports the right to freedom of religion or belief, which is restricted in Saudi Arabia; and thus it remains a Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office human rights priority country.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:37:31.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760241/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760241/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760241/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Sajaad Mohamed Abu Abdallah","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Saudi Arabian counterpart on the fatal shooting of Sajaad Mohammed Abdalla in Awamiya on 12 June 2017.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760242","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>The UK continues to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments. ​We encourage those with concerns about treatment in detention to report these to the relevant human rights oversight bodies.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:44:12.137Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760242/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760242/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760242/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Bahrain: Political Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Government of Bahrain on the provision of (a) adequate food, (b) medical care and (c) contact with family members for (i) all political prisoners, (ii) Ebtisam al-Saegh and (iii) Hajar Mansoor.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760243","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>​We encourage those with concerns about treatment in detention to report these to the relevant human rights oversight bodies. The UK continues to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:45:35.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760243/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760243/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760243/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Sayed Alwadaei","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to the Government of Bahrain about allegations of arbitrary arrest, detention and torture of relatives of Sayed Ahmend Al Wadaei.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760244","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>Our Ambassador to Saudi Arabia raised the operation in Awamiyah with the Government of Saudi Arabia on 26 July, including measures to guard against civilian casualties. The Saudi authorities underlined the seriousness it placed on fulfilling its responsibilities to all its citizens, including the Shia. We continue to monitor the situation in Awamiyah closely and we will continue to raise legitimate concerns at every appropriate opportunity. The British Government strongly supports the right to freedom of religion or belief, which is restricted in Saudi Arabia; and thus it remains a Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office human rights priority country.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:41:04.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760244/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760244/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760244/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Saudi Arabia: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he (a) has made and (b) plans to make to the Government of Saudi Arabia on adequate housing and compensation for civilians who have fled recent violence in Awamiya.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760246","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>Our Ambassador to Saudi Arabia raised the operation in Awamiyah with the Government of Saudi Arabia on 26 July, including measures to guard against civilian casualties. The Saudi authorities underlined the seriousness it placed on fulfilling its responsibilities to all its citizens, including the Shia. We continue to monitor the situation in Awamiyah closely and we will continue to raise legitimate concerns at every appropriate opportunity. The British Government strongly supports the right to freedom of religion or belief, which is restricted in Saudi Arabia; and thus it remains a Foreign and Commonwealth Office human rights priority country.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:42:31.013Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760246/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760246/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760246/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Saudi Arabia: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he (a) has made and (b) plans to make to the Government of Saudi Arabia on discrimination against Shiite citizens of that country, including in the town of Awamiya.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760247","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>It is the longstanding policy of successive UK Governments not to comment on intelligence matters.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T14:27:51.033Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760247/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760247/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760247/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Israel: Intelligence Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Israeli Government on intelligence-gathering targeting pro-Palestinian activists; whether he has requested any information from Israel about UK nationals; and whether he holds any information on the number of UK citizens affected by such intelligence gathering.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","105027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760248","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>We have not made any assessment. It is for Israel to decide its immigration policy. The UK's immigration policy is similarly protected. We have updated our travel advice recommending that concerned UK nationals contact the Israeli Embassy for further information.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T14:29:37.81Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760248/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760248/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760248/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Israel: Entry Clearances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effect on UK citizens of the Israeli laws which preclude entry to that country for pro-Palestinian activists, supporters of the Boycott Divestment and Sanctions Campaign and people who call for a ban on trade with illegal Israeli settlements.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","105028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760249","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>Our Ambassador to Saudi Arabia raised the operation in Awamiyah with the Government of Saudi Arabia on 26 July, including measures to guard against civilian casualties. The Saudi authorities underlined the seriousness it placed on fulfilling its responsibilities to all its citizens, including the Shia. We continue to monitor the situation in Awamiyah closely and we will continue to raise legitimate concerns at every appropriate opportunity. The British Government strongly supports the right to freedom of religion or belief, which is restricted in Saudi Arabia; and thus it remains a Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office human rights priority country.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:39:35.283Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760249/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760249/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760249/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Saudi Arabia: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Government of Saudi Arabia for a fair and thorough investigation into use of firearms by Saudi security forces during demolition of Awamiya's historic quarter and deaths of residents.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760250","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-13","<p>​​The British Government condemns all instances of discrimination and violence against individuals or groups because of their religion, regardless of the country or faith concerns. The UK engages with India on human rights issues, including religious freedom and minority rights, both bilaterally and through the EU. Our High Commission in New Delhi monitors the human rights situation in India and maintains a dialogue with the Indian National Commission for Minorities often via our Consulate General in the country.</p><p>FCO officials in New Delhi also regularly meet senior faith leaders to discuss issues such as religious tolerance, including most recently with a representative from a Christian organisation in India in June. The British Government also runs an array of projects in India to help promote minority rights and combat discrimination.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-10-13T12:31:11.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760250/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760250/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760250/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","India: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Indian counterpart on the treatment of Christians in India.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","105045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760252","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>​We encourage those with concerns about treatment in detention to report these to the relevant human rights oversight bodies. The UK continues to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:47:13.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760252/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760252/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760252/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Elias Faisal Al-Mulla","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Government of Bahrain on the provision of (a) adequate medical care and (b) contact with family members for Elias Faisal al-Mulla.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760253","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-12","<p>​There are no projects being funded by the Foreign and Commonwealth Office this financial year (2017/18) with either the Causeway Institute for Peace-building and Conflict Resolution (CIPCR) or the Bahrain Institute for Political Development (BIPD) for projects in Bahrain. The UK has worked with the Government of Bahrain to encourage progress on human rights in areas which include focusing on building effective and accountable institutions, strengthening the rule of law and justice reform. All of our work aims to support these institutions to operate in line with international standards, including on human rights, through sharing UK expertise and experience. Any training provided by, or on behalf of, the UK Government complies with our domestic and international human rights obligations and internal government guidance. As part of the programme process which CIPCR undertook between 2013-2016, there were a variety of events and meetings in Bahrain. CIPCR are not used for any project work in the former Yugoslavia.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-12T15:35:08.23Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760253/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760253/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760253/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-13","Causeway Institute for Peace-building and Conflict Resolution International","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what funding was allocated to the Causeway Institute for Peace-building and Conflict Resolution (CIPCR) for projects in the former Yugoslavia in 2017-18; how much his Department spent on training for the Bahrain Institute for Political Development (BIPD) in 2017-18; how many (a) workshops, (b) training events, (c) meetings and (d) other engagements between CIPCR and BIPD have taken place since 2012; on what dates and in which locations such events took place; and on what dates Overseas Security and Justice Guidance Assessments were conducted on those projects.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","105049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760254","Department of Health","false","2017-10-10","<p>The process for collecting data on attendances at accident and emergency departments due to intentional self-harm has not changed.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-10-10T12:58:37.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760254/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760254/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760254/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-13","Self-harm: Accident and Emergency Departments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 6 September 2017 to Question 6832, and with reference to the Answer of 14 November 2016 to Question 51973, whether the process for collection of data on the number of people who attended accident and emergency departments due to intentional self-harm has changed since the Answer of 14 November 2016.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","105042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760256","Department of Health","false","2017-10-10","<p>The latest information on the Mental Health Investment Standard (MHIS) is available in the Mental Health Five Year Forward View dashboard on the NHS England website. 2016-17 Q4 data is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/publication/mental-health-five-year-forward-view-dashboard//" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/publication/mental-health-five-year-forward-view-dashboard//</a></p><p>Performance on the MHIS is a key planning requirement and any clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) not achieving the target are required to give reasons which are then assessed as part of the planning, review and assurance process. NHS England also monitors performance on the MHIS throughout the year alongside performance on non-financial metrics. Where a commissioner fails to achieve the MHIS requirements without valid cause, NHS England may consider regulatory sanctions including in exceptional circumstances imposing directions on the CCGs to increase its level of investment.</p><p> </p><p>There are a number of reasons why a CCG may not meet the MHIS, including high investment in the mental health service in previous years, or high investment in other partner CCGs in their region, which would offset any decrease in investment.</p><p> </p><p>All reasons and evidence is reviewed locally by NHS England regional teams and nationally as part of internal assurance processes.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","105040 ; 105041","2017-10-10T13:03:24.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760256/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760256/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760256/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-13","Mental Health Services: Clinical Commissioning Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2017 to Question 9368, which clinical commissioning groups did not meet the Mental Health Investment Standard in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","105043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760257","Department of Health","false","2017-10-10","<p>The latest information on the Mental Health Investment Standard (MHIS) is available in the Mental Health Five Year Forward View dashboard on the NHS England website. 2016-17 Q4 data is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/publication/mental-health-five-year-forward-view-dashboard//" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/publication/mental-health-five-year-forward-view-dashboard//</a></p><p>Performance on the MHIS is a key planning requirement and any clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) not achieving the target are required to give reasons which are then assessed as part of the planning, review and assurance process. NHS England also monitors performance on the MHIS throughout the year alongside performance on non-financial metrics. Where a commissioner fails to achieve the MHIS requirements without valid cause, NHS England may consider regulatory sanctions including in exceptional circumstances imposing directions on the CCGs to increase its level of investment.</p><p> </p><p>There are a number of reasons why a CCG may not meet the MHIS, including high investment in the mental health service in previous years, or high investment in other partner CCGs in their region, which would offset any decrease in investment.</p><p> </p><p>All reasons and evidence is reviewed locally by NHS England regional teams and nationally as part of internal assurance processes.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","105040 ; 105043","2017-10-10T13:03:24.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760257/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760257/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760257/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-13","Mental Health Services: Clinical Commissioning Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2017 to Question