"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760260","Department of Health","false","2017-10-10","<p>The funding outlined in the 2017-18 NHS Mandate represents a £8.479 billion (8.3%) real terms increase on that set out in the 2013-14 Mandate.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-10-10T13:11:57.213Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760260/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760260/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760260/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-13","NHS: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the real terms increase was in NHS funding as set out in the NHS mandate between 2013-14 and 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke","10480"
